verbs.description: awestrike (third-person singular simple present awestrikes, present participle awestriking, simple past awestruck, past participle awestruck or awestricken)

entries.meaning: (transitive, now rare) To strike (someone) with awe; to make (someone) awestruck.
examples: Behold the God himself, whose dreadful brow
Awe-strikes the soul to speechless homage!
